cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.CY, cs.CR

This paper is about learning to rank with biased click data, which is a problem in information retrieval (IR). Therefore, cs.IR is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a new algorithm for jointly learning an unbiased ranker and an unbiased propensity model, which involves machine learning techniques such as inverse propensity weighting and online learning. This suggests that the paper may also belong to sub-categories such as cs.LG (machine learning), cs.CL (computation and language), cs.CY (computers and society), and cs.CR (cryptography and security).
